    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six. This naturally aspirated power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band peaking at its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain consists of a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. This example features essential preventative maintenance, including a reinforced rear subframe and a refreshed cooling system. The suspension maintains its intended kinematics with upgraded bushings for enhanced lateral stability. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains robust with documented valve clearances and consistent compression, offering a visceral, analog driving experience.",
