      "description": "Offered is a mechanically robust 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant with VarioCam Plus. This unit delivers a linear torque curve and 320hp through a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Critical preventative maintenance has been executed, including a ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive Rear Main Seal (RMS) replacement. The chassis retains its factory-spec kinematics with a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal glazing. Recent service includes a full cooling system pressure test and fresh synthetic lubricants. This is a high-revving, driver-focused machine with a clean DME overspeed report, ready for technical roads.",
